*(Please review it)*

In case the call to this function is huge, it is worth precomputing some stuff so that we can achieve O(1) time complexity of this function.

Numbers are 32-bits long, so we can split it in two (first 16-bits and second 16-bits)

Keep an array for answers of 16-bit numbers.

```
const int len = 1 << 16;
int f[len]; // this will store answers for 16-bit numbers

void precompute() {
	f[0] = 0;
	for(int i = 1; i < len; i++) {
		f[i] = f[i>>1] + (i&1);
	}
}

int hammingWeight(uint32_t n) {
	return f[n/len] + f[n%len]; // O(1) call
}
```

