Counting the number of 1 bits is the same as dropping the least significant bit until we find that n is now zero instead of whatever it was before.

Here's an example of how LSB works

n = 5 --> `101`

n = n & (n - 1) (**dropping LSB**)
n = 101 & (100) = 100

As you can see, we dropped the LSB by doing n - 1, and ANDing it with the n we had before the subtraction. 

Time Complexity: O(number of bits)

