solutions.content:
To use the function repeatedly, we will make an 8 bit look-up table and pass it with the input. The 32-bit unsigned integer will be split into 4 equal parts and each part will be looked up in O(1) time.

The look-up table can be easily built as:

	int[] lookup = new int[256];
	for(int i = 0; i <= 255; i++){
		lookup[i] = (i & 1) + lookup[i / 2];
	}

The function can be modified as :
```
public class Solution {
    // you need to treat n as an unsigned value
    public int hammingWeight(int n, int[] lookup) {
        int count = lookup[n & 0xff] + lookup[(n >> 8) & 0xff] + 
            lookup[(n >> 16) & 0xff] + lookup[(n >> 24) & 0xff];
        return count;
    }
}
```

