# Using BitMasking
```
public int hammingWeight(int n) {
//         using bit masking
        int count = 0, i = 0;
        while(i < 32){
            int mask = (1 << i++);
            if((n & mask) != 0) count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
```

# Right Shift Operation
```
public int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while(n != 0){
            if((n & 1) != 0) count++;
            n >>>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
```
# Using hamming distance method
*  Do & operation of that number with n-1 till num != 0
*  eg -
		num = 123
		num = num&(num-1) = 123 & 122 => 122
		num = num&(num-1) = 122 & 121 => 120
		num = num&(num-1) = 120 & 119 => 112
		num = num&(num-1) = 112 & 111 => 96
		num = num&(num-1) = 96 & 95 => 64
		num = num&(num-1) = 64 & 63 => 0
```
public int hammingWeight(int n) {
//         using hamming distance method
        int count = 0;
        while(n != 0){
            count++;
            n = (n & (n-1));
        }
        return count;
    }
```

