The Solution is Based on **Brian Kernighan’s Algorithm:**  
The Kernighan’s Algorithm jumps on only selective bits which are set (1).
What we are generally Doing here is finding out the right most set bit which is set i.e.  is 1 
    which is calculated using "n & -n" and then we subtract this from rsb so that the set bit will become non set now following by counting the set bit.
    And we count till all the bits become 0 and at the end we return the counted set bits.

